<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>But so are you...</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Seoman Snowlock">Seoman Snowlock</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:03 a.m. 23/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> But so are you...<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1947" TARGET=_self>Make No Mistake, You Are Wrong</A> (The RealmWeaver)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>CC NEVER intentionally kills someone exclusively with DoT to make them lose xp. I've even gone so far as to heal a target who was rooted underwater so he didn't lose xp. Please research your claims before you hop on the bandwagon.

<P>Seo, who knows the difference between being a hardass and just being an asshole.
<P>&gt; DOT Spells are currently a bannable offense on the PVP server
<BR>&gt; because they allow players to kill other players and also cause
<BR>&gt; them to lose experience, an affect normal kills do not usually
<BR>&gt; have. While you might not intend this, there ARE indeed players
<BR>&gt; who take advantage of this. Nafgar of CC is one of them. He
<BR>&gt; claims that it is the "only way" they can fight back
<BR>&gt; against people, yet CC contains a majority of incredibly
<BR>&gt; powerful wizards with DD spells, instead they stand back and DOT
<BR>&gt; people, causing them to lose EXP and sometimes levels. In short,
<BR>&gt; don't kid yourself, this is no joke, do not DOT other players.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><EM><A HREF="http://www.covetouscrew.org" TARGET=_top>CC</A></EM></P>
